1
00:00:10,033 --> 00:00:11,900
<i>Is this really your collateral?</i>

2
00:00:12,033 --> 00:00:14,167
<i>-Dad, please!
-We don't have any other choice.</i>

3
00:00:14,300 --> 00:00:16,033
<i>I won't just be payment
for a debt.</i>

4
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:17,367
<i> I'll play the game.</i>

5
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:18,567
<i> Let's rework the gown, okay?</i>

6
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:20,867
<i>Let's change the fabric,
let's change the neckline,</i>

7
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,733
<i> let's change the bride.</i>

8
00:00:22,867 --> 00:00:24,967
<i>You've endured
quite a lot to get here.</i>

9
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:30,067
<i>Are you sure that
this is what you really want?</i>

10
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:31,500
<i> Good luck to Marj, then.</i>

11
00:00:31,633 --> 00:00:34,500
<i>I'm going to win over
the entire Torrecampo family.</i>

12
00:00:34,667 --> 00:00:36,933
<i> And Edward will be my way in.</i>

13
00:00:37,067 --> 00:00:40,433
<i>If you think this wedding
makes you one of us,</i>

14
00:00:40,567 --> 00:00:41,400
<i> you're wrong.</i>

15
00:00:41,533 --> 00:00:43,000
<i> You can still walk away</i>

16
00:00:43,133 --> 00:00:44,967
<i>while you still have
some dignity left.</i>

17
00:00:58,333 --> 00:01:01,700
Sir, excuse me.
There's just a short delay.

18
00:01:01,833 --> 00:01:02,800
Where is she?

19
00:01:02,933 --> 00:01:04,933
Sir, she was on standby earlier
in the bridal car.

20
00:01:05,067 --> 00:01:06,500
But she suddenly disappeared.

21
00:01:07,933 --> 00:01:09,133
What? Where did she go?

22
00:01:09,267 --> 00:01:10,767
Just a moment, Sir.
Have you found her?

23
00:01:10,900 --> 00:01:12,533
Check the restroom.

24
00:01:12,667 --> 00:01:14,033
Sir, please wait.

25
00:04:28,967 --> 00:04:30,700
Marj.

26
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:37,000
Your face is glowing now.

27
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:57,033
Jobert.

28
00:04:57,167 --> 00:04:58,567
Paolo.

29
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,633
I'll take your sister, okay?

30
00:05:13,467 --> 00:05:14,833
You scared me back there.

31
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:18,100
I thought you left me.

32
00:05:21,667 --> 00:05:23,533
I just needed to be sure...

33
00:05:24,667 --> 00:05:27,767
that I can do this
no matter how hard it gets.

34
00:05:29,533 --> 00:05:30,900
For us.

35
00:05:31,967 --> 00:05:34,300
For the family
we're going to build.

36
00:05:50,167 --> 00:05:52,267
<i> We are gathered here today</i>

37
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:55,867
<i>to witness and celebrate
the union of two hearts,</i>

38
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,867
Paolo and Marjorie,

39
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:01,467
<i>as they begin their life
together as husband and wife.</i>

40
00:06:02,533 --> 00:06:07,633
Today, we honor their promise
before God, their families,

41
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:09,200
<i> and everyone they love.</i>

42
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:16,700
Hello, everyone.

43
00:06:20,133 --> 00:06:22,033
We're so sorry.

44
00:06:22,167 --> 00:06:25,433
Please, go on. Don't mind us.

45
00:06:29,733 --> 00:06:31,100
Thea?

46
00:06:34,667 --> 00:06:35,867
You know her?

47
00:06:58,400 --> 00:07:00,033
Okay, smile.

48
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:02,800
Closer.

49
00:07:03,833 --> 00:07:04,667
<i> Smile.</i>

50
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,100
<i> Mom.</i>

51
00:07:06,233 --> 00:07:07,967
Edward!

52
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:11,300
Oh, it's so nice to see you.

53
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:14,467
Dad.

54
00:07:18,633 --> 00:07:21,133
You barely show up,

55
00:07:21,267 --> 00:07:24,433
and you almost ruined
your brother's wedding.

56
00:07:24,567 --> 00:07:25,967
Miss you, too, Dad.

57
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:29,800
Anyway,

58
00:07:29,933 --> 00:07:32,767
Mom, Dad,
this is Thea Villareal.

59
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:34,633
Thea, these are my parents.

60
00:07:34,767 --> 00:07:36,967
Greg and Regina Torrecampo.

61
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:38,600
- Hello.
- Hello, nice to meet you.

62
00:07:38,733 --> 00:07:40,100
- You look beautiful.
- Thank you.

63
00:07:40,233 --> 00:07:41,900
Villareal?

64
00:07:42,033 --> 00:07:46,133
Are you related to the
Villareals from Batangas?

65
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:50,433
Yes. Yes, I am.

66
00:07:50,567 --> 00:07:53,133
I'm glad to finally meet you.

67
00:07:53,267 --> 00:07:55,933
Edward, is she your...

68
00:07:56,067 --> 00:07:57,733
She's a...

69
00:07:57,867 --> 00:07:59,267
very special someone.

70
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:05,467
She's actually the one
who convinced me to come home.

71
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:09,400
Then thank you for bringing
our youngest back to us.

72
00:08:09,533 --> 00:08:11,267
It's easy to convince someone
to come home

73
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:14,500
when the family
is as wonderful as yours.

74
00:08:14,633 --> 00:08:16,767
Then welcome
to our wonderful family.

75
00:08:16,900 --> 00:08:18,300
Thank you.

76
00:08:21,933 --> 00:08:25,067
Oh, Marj,
it's nice to see you again.

77
00:08:28,433 --> 00:08:30,367
Wait...

78
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:32,567
do you know each other?

79
00:08:32,700 --> 00:08:35,400
We used to work together.

80
00:08:35,533 --> 00:08:37,600
But we were rivals back then.

81
00:08:37,733 --> 00:08:39,733
You know how it is
in the real estate industry.

82
00:08:39,867 --> 00:08:42,567
Everyone wants to be first.
Everyone wants the spotlight.

83
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:44,500
But that was a long time ago.

84
00:08:47,767 --> 00:08:53,000
Marj, I hope this time
we can just support each other.

85
00:08:53,133 --> 00:08:54,967
No more competition, please.

86
00:09:01,167 --> 00:09:02,767
Torrecampo family, your turn.

87
00:09:02,900 --> 00:09:03,833
Okay, okay.

88
00:09:03,967 --> 00:09:05,033
- I'll let you have your moment.
- Oh, all right.

89
00:09:05,167 --> 00:09:06,667
I'll see you later.

90
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:09,267
Thank you.

91
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:10,900
<i> Thank you.</i>

92
00:09:21,467 --> 00:09:22,967
Okay, everyone, closer.

93
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,067
Okay.

94
00:09:25,567 --> 00:09:27,000
Smile.

95
00:09:28,900 --> 00:09:30,200
<i> All I need is perfect timing.</i>

96
00:09:30,333 --> 00:09:33,900
<i>I'll be in that family picture
soon enough.</i>

97
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,800
Bro.

98
00:09:51,933 --> 00:09:53,800
Didn't expect
you'd actually show up.

99
00:09:53,933 --> 00:09:55,267
Without a grand entrance.

100
00:09:56,667 --> 00:09:58,500
I thought...

101
00:09:58,633 --> 00:10:00,000
you were still mad at me.

102
00:10:01,433 --> 00:10:02,767
I'm not here because of you.

103
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:06,767
I came because of Marj.

104
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:09,133
We go way back. We're friends.

105
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:13,467
Thank you.

106
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:15,367
We'll wait for you outside,
okay?

107
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:17,167
Thank you.

108
00:10:27,233 --> 00:10:28,700
Can I come in?

109
00:10:32,733 --> 00:10:34,100
Why are you here?

110
00:10:35,933 --> 00:10:37,233
Small world, right?

111
00:10:37,367 --> 00:10:39,367
Who would've thought
that your brother-in-law

112
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:40,967
would end up
being the love of my life?

113
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:42,900
Love of your life?

114
00:10:43,033 --> 00:10:45,367
You just met Edward.

115
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:47,900
How can you say
you already love him?

116
00:10:48,033 --> 00:10:49,233
Well,

117
00:10:50,367 --> 00:10:52,133
I'm happy you finally
have a girlfriend.

118
00:10:55,133 --> 00:10:58,767
And maybe now
that you're moving on,

119
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:01,100
maybe...

120
00:11:01,233 --> 00:11:04,433
we can finally forget
what happened between us.

121
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:12,867
Marj, I'm not here to compare
notes on the Torrecampo boys.

122
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:15,233
<i>I know this isn't the best time,</i>

123
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:18,267
but...

124
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:20,633
I want to make peace with you.

125
00:11:20,767 --> 00:11:22,900
I know I hurt you badly.

126
00:11:23,033 --> 00:11:24,400
But that was a long time ago.

127
00:11:25,867 --> 00:11:30,233
I was young, stupid,
and insecure.

128
00:11:31,733 --> 00:11:34,133
And I truly regret
what happened between us.

129
00:11:36,100 --> 00:11:38,167
Marj...

130
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:40,300
can we just put it behind us?

131
00:11:40,433 --> 00:11:41,933
Do you really think...

132
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:44,533
it's that easy
to forget everything?

133
00:11:46,967 --> 00:11:48,667
Bro...

134
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:51,333
can't you just be happy?

135
00:11:51,467 --> 00:11:52,500
For Marj.

136
00:11:54,533 --> 00:11:56,800
That's not the issue.

137
00:11:56,933 --> 00:12:00,633
You stealing Marj from me
was just the tipping point.

138
00:12:02,833 --> 00:12:04,267
Even before that,

139
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:06,233
I was always the one losing
because of you.

140
00:12:07,967 --> 00:12:11,533
I don't want any more tension.
I just want us to be okay.

141
00:12:11,667 --> 00:12:13,433
I don't have any other agenda.

142
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:17,067
You want me to forget?

143
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:19,400
Easy for you to say.

144
00:12:19,533 --> 00:12:22,667
I didn't just lose my job
because of you.

145
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:26,100
You destroyed my name,
my reputation.

146
00:12:27,133 --> 00:12:30,400
You're the reason
my life fell apart.

147
00:12:30,533 --> 00:12:33,600
You know that.
So, Paolo, please.

148
00:12:33,733 --> 00:12:37,100
Let's not force something
that's already broken.

149
00:12:39,533 --> 00:12:40,967
<i> I know.</i>

150
00:12:41,100 --> 00:12:43,433
<i> And I'm sorry.</i>

151
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:46,700
I don't even know
what I was thinking back then.

152
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:49,533
I don't need your apology, Thea.

153
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:52,433
If you managed to fool Edward
with that act,

154
00:12:52,567 --> 00:12:54,767
don't think
you can fool me, too.

155
00:12:54,900 --> 00:12:57,633
And don't think you can
manipulate the Torrecampos,

156
00:12:57,767 --> 00:12:59,200
or Edward.

157
00:12:59,333 --> 00:13:01,433
Marj...

158
00:13:01,567 --> 00:13:03,567
please.

159
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:07,000
Just give me one chance
to prove myself.

160
00:13:07,133 --> 00:13:09,400
I don't believe you've changed.

161
00:13:10,567 --> 00:13:11,633
If you're here

162
00:13:11,767 --> 00:13:14,467
trying to prove there's
still something good in you,

163
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:15,967
you're wasting your time.

164
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:18,700
Marj, please.

165
00:13:27,133 --> 00:13:28,167
Mrs. Torrecampo,

166
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:31,300
we still need photos
with your mother and brother.

167
00:13:41,067 --> 00:13:45,833
Enjoy the spotlight while
it lasts, Mrs. Torrecampo.

168
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:21,300
She seems to be doing this
on purpose.

169
00:14:21,433 --> 00:14:23,367
Why did she have to show up now?

170
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:26,433
Why today of all days?

171
00:14:28,767 --> 00:14:33,333
Why does something always happen
to ruin my happiness?

172
00:14:35,767 --> 00:14:37,233
But, Marj...

173
00:14:37,367 --> 00:14:40,667
maybe she really
has changed?

174
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:43,867
Maybe you need to learn...

175
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,900
to trust people, too,
sweetheart.

176
00:14:47,567 --> 00:14:52,433
Maybe this is the right time
for forgiveness.

177
00:14:52,567 --> 00:14:54,833
For things to finally be fixed.

178
00:14:56,167 --> 00:14:57,600
Mom...

179
00:14:57,733 --> 00:15:00,900
some people don't deserve
a second chance.

180
00:15:07,267 --> 00:15:08,300
Mom.

181
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:11,100
Are you okay?

182
00:15:12,967 --> 00:15:14,700
Marj.

183
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:16,833
Marj, please don't be mad at me.
Marj.

184
00:15:19,233 --> 00:15:22,033
Dad? Dad's here.

185
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:28,533
What is he doing here?

186
00:15:28,667 --> 00:15:32,867
Marj, I'm the one
who asked him to come.

187
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:35,733
Maybe it's time for you
and your father to talk.

188
00:15:35,900 --> 00:15:39,667
You can't stay like this
forever, Marj.

189
00:15:46,567 --> 00:15:48,533
Marj, sweetheart.

190
00:15:48,667 --> 00:15:50,433
I'm sorry.

191
00:15:50,567 --> 00:15:52,333
I just wanted to make it up
to you

192
00:15:52,467 --> 00:15:55,500
and be with you
on your wedding day.

193
00:16:05,367 --> 00:16:07,467
Should we make up with dad now?

194
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:10,267
Be a family again?

195
00:16:13,133 --> 00:16:14,800
Take care of him, Mom, okay?

196
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:15,867
Marj.

197
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:19,167
I need to take care
of my other guests.

198
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:20,500
Excuse me.

199
00:16:50,133 --> 00:16:51,800
Hi, Sir.

200
00:16:51,933 --> 00:16:53,300
Mind if I join you?

201
00:16:56,167 --> 00:16:58,467
You're Marj's father, right?

202
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:02,233
I'm Thea, Marj's friend.

203
00:17:05,267 --> 00:17:06,667
A friend of Marj's?

204
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:10,567
Sorry about that.

205
00:17:10,700 --> 00:17:12,433
I don't really remember you.

206
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:15,700
Then again,

207
00:17:15,867 --> 00:17:20,300
there's a lot I don't know
about my own daughter.

208
00:17:20,433 --> 00:17:24,200
But why weren't you
at the ceremony earlier?

209
00:17:24,333 --> 00:17:26,133
That's such a shame, Sir.

210
00:17:26,267 --> 00:17:28,600
You didn't even get
to walk her down the aisle.

211
00:17:29,933 --> 00:17:32,133
They didn't even mention
your name in the speech.

212
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:39,433
And your seat was far
from the family table.

213
00:17:44,133 --> 00:17:46,267
Well...

214
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,300
my daughter's still very upset
with me.

215
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:51,767
If that's what she wants,

216
00:17:52,933 --> 00:17:53,933
then I'll let her be.

217
00:17:54,067 --> 00:17:55,467
As long as she's happy.

218
00:17:56,500 --> 00:18:00,600
But, Sir, no matter what,
you're still her father.

219
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:05,667
You're already the one
lowering yourself,

220
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:09,233
and yet somehow
you're still the bad guy?

221
00:18:09,367 --> 00:18:12,267
Honestly, Sir,
that doesn't seem right.

222
00:18:14,133 --> 00:18:17,033
Marj's pretty harsh.

223
00:18:17,167 --> 00:18:19,167
Like it's so easy for her
to forget

224
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:21,667
that she owes her life to you.

225
00:18:25,567 --> 00:18:28,433
Maybe because she married
someone who's rich.

226
00:18:29,867 --> 00:18:33,067
She probably thinks she can
erase you from her life now.

227
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:35,167
You know...

228
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,900
you're not wrong.

229
00:18:38,033 --> 00:18:40,300
If it weren't for me,

230
00:18:40,433 --> 00:18:42,333
she wouldn't even be
in this world.

231
00:18:43,767 --> 00:18:46,933
Exactly!

232
00:18:47,067 --> 00:18:49,100
Sir, even if you're fighting,

233
00:18:49,233 --> 00:18:52,367
you still deserve respect.

234
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:54,133
Even as Marj's friend,

235
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:57,000
I'd never tolerate that kind
of behavior if she were wrong.

236
00:18:58,067 --> 00:19:01,767
Just because
she's a Torrecampo now

237
00:19:01,900 --> 00:19:05,100
doesn't mean she gets
to disrespect you.

238
00:19:11,867 --> 00:19:13,700
Yeah.

239
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,167
No matter what,

240
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:17,667
I'm still her father.

241
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:24,367
She shouldn't be treating me
like just another guest here.

242
00:19:26,767 --> 00:19:32,767
Sir, you need to remind your
daughter where she came from.

243
00:19:37,033 --> 00:19:39,733
Please raise your glasses
for the newlyweds.

244
00:19:39,867 --> 00:19:45,667
To my son Paolo and
my daughter-in-law, Marjorie.

245
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:51,700
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

246
00:19:56,667 --> 00:19:58,000
<i> Wait a second!</i>

247
00:19:59,933 --> 00:20:01,433
<i> My turn.</i>

248
00:20:05,733 --> 00:20:07,633
I've got something to say.

249
00:20:20,833 --> 00:20:22,267
Lito, stop it.

250
00:20:25,233 --> 00:20:26,800
Lito, have some shame.

251
00:20:26,933 --> 00:20:29,567
<i> Why?</i>

252
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:31,600
Have some mercy
on your daughter, Lito.

253
00:20:33,300 --> 00:20:35,900
Lito, listen to me.

254
00:20:36,067 --> 00:20:38,000
- Stop it.
- What?

255
00:20:44,967 --> 00:20:46,667
Hey, Marj!

256
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:48,500
Congratulations.

257
00:20:48,633 --> 00:20:50,400
You know what?

258
00:20:50,533 --> 00:20:52,367
I've got a lot of resentment
toward you.

259
00:20:54,233 --> 00:20:59,767
You didn't even let me
walk you down the aisle.

260
00:21:01,267 --> 00:21:03,033
You didn't even say,

261
00:21:03,167 --> 00:21:04,800
"Hey, Dad...

262
00:21:04,933 --> 00:21:08,600
thanks for coming
to my wedding."

263
00:21:11,933 --> 00:21:14,267
Now...

264
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:17,333
that you're married
to a rich man,

265
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:20,900
you've changed!

266
00:21:24,900 --> 00:21:26,067
Lito, listen to me.

267
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:28,033
- Lito, listen to me.
- Just a second!

268
00:21:28,167 --> 00:21:29,633
- You're embarrassing yourself.
- You don't even know...

269
00:21:31,533 --> 00:21:34,933
how to look back
at where you came from!

270
00:21:35,067 --> 00:21:36,267
Dad, stop it!

271
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:38,100
Why are you shutting me up?

272
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:43,567
Just because you covered
for all my...

273
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:49,233
- That's enough, Lito.
- failures, you think you have

274
00:21:49,367 --> 00:21:52,933
the right to humiliate me
in front of your guests?

275
00:21:53,067 --> 00:21:55,267
Lito, stop it! Stop!

276
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:56,633
- Have some shame!
- What is wrong with you?

277
00:21:56,767 --> 00:21:59,433
That's enough, Lito! Enough!

278
00:22:06,733 --> 00:22:09,333
So loud.

279
00:22:10,667 --> 00:22:12,400
Jobert.

280
00:22:19,067 --> 00:22:20,767
Enough!

281
00:22:30,167 --> 00:22:32,000
<i> Enough, Lito!</i>

282
00:22:39,967 --> 00:22:41,833
Marj, I'm sorry.

283
00:22:41,967 --> 00:22:44,300
<i> I'm so sorry, Marj.</i>

284
00:22:44,433 --> 00:22:47,100
That's enough, Lito.

285
00:22:55,333 --> 00:22:59,400
Marj. Marj, I'm really sorry,
sweetheart.

286
00:22:59,533 --> 00:23:00,500
I'm sorry.

287
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:04,667
I'm sorry, honey.

288
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:08,300
I never thought your father
would go this far.

289
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:17,133
Marj, I never wanted to ruin
your wedding like this.

290
00:23:17,267 --> 00:23:19,200
I know you didn't want this
to happen, Mom.

291
00:23:19,333 --> 00:23:21,467
But I'm hurt, too.

292
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:23,633
There were so many guests.

293
00:23:23,800 --> 00:23:24,933
So many people
saw what happened.

294
00:23:25,067 --> 00:23:26,467
It wasn't just me
who was humiliated.

295
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:28,367
Paolo's family was, too.

296
00:23:29,500 --> 00:23:32,067
Marj, don't worry.

297
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:33,600
Don't worry.

298
00:23:33,733 --> 00:23:35,033
I'll take your father home.

299
00:23:35,167 --> 00:23:37,900
I'll make him leave.

300
00:23:38,033 --> 00:23:40,333
Marj, I'm begging you.

301
00:23:40,467 --> 00:23:43,500
Please don't be mad
at your dad anymore.

302
00:23:43,633 --> 00:23:45,967
He's just drunk, Marj.

303
00:23:47,567 --> 00:23:50,167
He was drunk when
he left us, too.

304
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:53,000
He was also drunk
when he hurt us, Mom!

305
00:23:53,133 --> 00:23:54,033
So please, Mom.

306
00:23:54,167 --> 00:23:56,167
Stop pushing me
to make peace with him,

307
00:23:56,333 --> 00:23:59,067
because that will never happen.

308
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:01,133
I don't want to see him
ever again!

309
00:24:01,267 --> 00:24:03,467
Marj. Calm down, Love.

310
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:05,933
- Calm down.
- Marj.

311
00:24:09,033 --> 00:24:11,833
I'll just talk to your father.

312
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:23,233
I'm really sorry, Love.

313
00:24:23,367 --> 00:24:24,333
I'm sorry.

314
00:24:25,967 --> 00:24:28,433
I wanted this day
to be memorable,

315
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:31,933
but I don't know why so many
people are trying to ruin it.

316
00:24:33,733 --> 00:24:34,700
Hey.

317
00:24:37,300 --> 00:24:39,967
Let's not make a big deal
out of what happened, okay?

318
00:24:41,033 --> 00:24:42,867
Let's just enjoy
the rest of the night.

319
00:24:44,300 --> 00:24:45,767
Come on.

320
00:24:45,900 --> 00:24:49,467
The guests are waiting
for us inside.

321
00:24:49,600 --> 00:24:50,633
Love, I'm sorry.

322
00:24:50,767 --> 00:24:54,700
But can I stay here for a bit?

323
00:24:54,833 --> 00:24:55,700
I just...

324
00:24:55,833 --> 00:24:57,733
I just need to calm myself down.

325
00:24:57,867 --> 00:25:00,167
I don't want to break down
in front of everyone.

326
00:25:02,100 --> 00:25:04,333
Are you sure?

327
00:25:04,467 --> 00:25:07,100
I can stay with you.

328
00:25:07,233 --> 00:25:09,000
No. I promise.

329
00:25:09,133 --> 00:25:12,233
I'll go back in once I'm okay.

330
00:25:14,367 --> 00:25:15,567
Okay.

331
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:22,133
When you're ready, okay?

332
00:25:22,267 --> 00:25:23,667
I'll wait for you.

333
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:08,333
Tomorrow, we leave
for our honeymoon.

334
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:09,600
When we get back,

335
00:26:09,733 --> 00:26:12,233
we'll go straight to the
Torrecampo house with Jobert.

336
00:26:12,367 --> 00:26:14,700
If you want us to accept you,

337
00:26:14,833 --> 00:26:16,500
you're the one
who needs to adjust.

338
00:26:16,633 --> 00:26:19,267
Learn how to fit in.

339
00:26:22,500 --> 00:26:25,100
That place is not for me.

340
00:26:25,233 --> 00:26:26,967
And it's definitely not for you.

341
00:26:27,100 --> 00:26:29,333
Can you just leave me alone?

342
00:26:29,467 --> 00:26:32,333
You know what? My instincts
about Paolo were right.

343
00:26:32,467 --> 00:26:34,700
There's nothing special
about him.

344
00:26:34,833 --> 00:26:37,067
Why are you suddenly so curious
about my brother?

345
00:26:40,167 --> 00:26:42,267
I'll see you around.
